<section id="why-trackie" class="mt-[84px] px-[4px]">
  <div class="rounded-[22px] border border-[rgba(43,39,36,0.07)] bg-white px-[30px] py-[38px] sm:px-[44px]">
    <div>
      <h2 class="m-0 text-[24px] font-extrabold tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink">
        Why "Trackie", and not "Actual Budget"?
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-[16px] text-[16.5px] leading-[1.65] text-pretty text-muted">
        A couple of reasons. It's a simple, friendly name that's easy to say and
        pass on to a mate, and while we are using the official open-source <a
          href="https://actualbudget.org/"
          class="underline underline-offset-2">Actual Budget</a
        >, we don't want to make it seem like we are endorsed by the project.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
